# FRIDA Excel Reader Rules

## Workbook Lifecycle

`Excel NewWB` creates an in-memory workbook - it is NOT saved until you explicitly call `Save` or `SaveAs`.

```
Excel NewWB as WB
Excel NewWSheet WB as WS
## ... work with workbook ...
Excel SaveAs WB path "C:\output\report.xlsx"
Excel Close WB
```

## Checkpointing

For long processes, save after each processed item to enable recovery:

```
foreach item in itemList {
    ## Process item
    try
        ## ... business logic ...
        Excel Append from WSProcessed at [1 ="<<<itemId>>>", 2 ="SUCCESS", 3 ="<<<timestamp>>>"]
    catch as ex
        Excel Append from WSProcessed at [1 ="<<<itemId>>>", 2 ="FAIL", 3 ="<<<ex>>>"]
    end
    Excel Save WB
}
```

## Always Close Workbooks

```
## Save and close
Excel Save WB and close

## Or separately
Excel Save WB
Excel Close WB
```

## Header Validation

When scripts depend on specific columns, validate headers before processing:

```
Excel ReadCell from the worksheet WS from the cell {1,1} and save its value as {header1}
if ("<<<header1>>>" -ne "Expected Header")
    Finish "Template mismatch: expected 'Expected Header' in A1"
end
```

## Resume Strategy

Maintain a Processed log sheet to enable resuming interrupted runs:

```
#%region RESUME_LOGIC
Excel LoadWBook "<<<filePath>>>" as WB
Excel LoadWSheet WB sheet "Processed" as WSProcessed

## Count already processed items
Excel ReadColumn from the worksheet {WSProcessed} with the column index {1} start_at {2} and save its value as {processed} visible without nulls
CountItems in processed and save_as totalProcessed

## Calculate starting row in Template sheet
MathOperation <<<totalProcessed>>> + 2 and save as startRow
#%endregion
```
